Tailwind v4 (CSS <code>@theme</code>)Tailwind v3 (<code>tailwind.config.js</code>) <pre><code>@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-brand: #2563eb;
  --font-display: "Inter", sans-serif;
  --spacing-18: 4.5rem;
}
</code></pre> <p>These tokens automatically create utilities like <code>bg-brand</code>, <code>font-display</code>, and <code>p-18</code>.</p> <pre><code>export default {
  content: ['./index.html', './src/**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx}'],
  theme: {
    extend: {
      colors: { brand: '#2563eb' },
      fontFamily: { display: ['Inter', 'sans-serif'] },
      spacing: { 18: '4.5rem' },
    },
  },
  plugins: [],
};
</code></pre>

Strategy Behavior Best for Cache First Return cache if present; only hit network on a miss. Hashed/immutable static assets, fonts. Network First Try network; fall back to cache on failure/timeout. Frequently-changing API data. Stale-While-Revalidate Return cache immediately, fetch in background to update for next time. Avatars, feeds—speed over freshness. Network Only Always go to network. Non-cacheable / sensitive requests. Cache Only Always serve from cache. Assets known to be pre-cached. <p>Raw implementations:</p> <pre><code>// Cache First
async function cacheFirst(request) {
  const cached = await caches.match(request);
  if (cached) return cached;
  const response = await fetch(request);
  const cache = await caches.open('static-v1');
  cache.put(request, response.clone());
  return response;
}

// Network First (with cache fallback)
async function networkFirst(request) {
  const cache = await caches.open('api-v1');
  try {
    const response = await fetch(request);
    cache.put(request, response.clone());
    return response;
  } catch {
    return (await cache.match(request)) ?? Response.error();
  }
}

// Stale-While-Revalidate
async function staleWhileRevalidate(request) {
  const cache = await caches.open('swr-v1');
  const cached = await cache.match(request);
  const networkPromise = fetch(request).then((response) =&gt; {
    cache.put(request, response.clone());
    return response;
  });
  return cached ?? networkPromise; // serve cache now, update in background
}
</code></pre> <p>With Workbox / <code>vite-plugin-pwa</code>, the same strategies are declarative via <code>runtimeCaching</code>:</p> <pre><code>// inside VitePWA({ workbox: { ... } })
runtimeCaching: [
  {
    urlPattern: ({ request }) =&gt; request.destination === 'image',
    handler: 'StaleWhileRevalidate',
    options: { cacheName: 'images', expiration: { maxEntries: 60 } },
  },
  {
    urlPattern: ({ url }) =&gt; url.pathname.startsWith('/api/'),
    handler: 'NetworkFirst',
    options: {
      cacheName: 'api',
      networkTimeoutSeconds: 5,
      expiration: { maxAgeSeconds: 60 * 5 },
    },
  },
],
</code></pre> <p>Managing cached data</p> <p>Version your cache names (<code>static-v1</code> → <code>static-v2</code>) and delete old ones in <code>activate</code>. Cap growth with Workbox's <code>expiration</code> plugin (<code>maxEntries</code> / <code>maxAgeSeconds</code>). Remember caches count against the origin's storage quota; request <code>navigator.storage.persist()</code> for data you must not lose to eviction.</p>

